if n = 1, r = g = b = 0
and no of ways to fill will be 3 (R, G or B)

if n = 2, r = g = b = 0
and no of ways to fill will be 6 (RG, GR, GB, BG, RB, BR)

if n >= 3 then r = g = b = n/3
and no of ways to fill will be
n! / ( (n/3)! X (n/3)! X (n/3)! ) if n%3 = 0
3 X (n!) / ( (n/3)! X (n/3)! X (n/3 + 1)! ) if n%3 = 1
3 X ( (n!) / ( (n/3)! X (n/3)! X (n/3 + 2)! ) +
(n!) / ( (n/3)! X (n/3 + 1)! X (n/3 + 1)! ) ) if n%3 = 2
